caption: I like this place. It is very Italian. Even the leather benches resemble all the colors of the Italian flag. Regarding the food it is awesome. I called in an order for delivery - toasted ravioli meal with bread and a side salad. I was told the total was $17.50. The math didn’t add up but I thought maybe there was a delivery fee. It was delivered an hour later & it was WRONG! It was a big salad with old, brown lettuce drowning in dressing & onions (it was not edible) and 8 pieces of cold toasted ravioli (which I’m pretty sure were frozen Luigis) with a small cup of cold marinara...obviously the appetizer portion. And a piece of store-bought rainbow cake...which I didn’t even order. I tipped the delivery guy $4.50 for a total of $22. WHAT A WASTE OF MONEY! Yes...I should’ve checked it before he left...that’s on me. BUT for delivery I would NOT recommend this place.
